Google Colab and Machine Learning

  • Go to the project folder:
cd "%USERPROFILE%\Documents" && cd yolo_projects
  • Activate the environment
cd venv39 && Scripts\activate
  • start the label-studio, (*Need to change to your folder path)
SET DATA_UPLOAD_MAX_NUMBER_FILES=10000

set LOCAL_FILES_SERVING_ENABLED=true

set LABEL_STUDIO_LOCAL_FILES_DOCUMENT_ROOT=%USERPROFILE%\\Documents\\yolo_projects\\datasets

or 

set LABEL_STUDIO_LOCAL_FILES_DOCUMENT_ROOT=C:\\Users\\YOUR_USER_NAME\\Documents\\yolo_projects\\datasets

***Change YOUR_USER_NAME from the path

Label-studio start

  • upload the images to /content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/export-dir/images

  • Run this to split and move your data. so 2nd Code Section, run this:

import os

import shutil

import random

  

# Paths

source_images = '/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/export-dir/images'

source_labels = '/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/export-dir/labels'

dest = '/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/dataset'

train_ratio = 0.8

  

# Get all image files

images = [f for f in os.listdir(source_images) if f.endswith(('.jpg', '.png'))]

random.shuffle(images)

  

# Split

train_size = int(len(images) * train_ratio)

train_images = images[:train_size]

val_images = images[train_size:]

  

# Helper function

def copy_files(file_list, split):

    os.makedirs(f'{dest}/images/{split}', exist_ok=True)

    os.makedirs(f'{dest}/labels/{split}', exist_ok=True)

    for img in file_list:

        base = os.path.splitext(img)[0]

        shutil.copy(f'{source_images}/{img}', f'{dest}/images/{split}/{img}')

        shutil.copy(f'{source_labels}/{base}.txt', f'{dest}/labels/{split}/{base}.txt')

  

copy_files(train_images, 'train')

copy_files(val_images, 'val')
  • Create the Dataset YAML File
data_yaml = """

train: /content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/dataset/images/train

val: /content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/dataset/images/val

  

nc: 3

names: ['Garbage','garbage','rubbish']

"""

  

with open("/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/data.yaml", "w") as f:

    f.write(data_yaml)

  • Train the model
from ultralytics import YOLO

  

# This will automatically download yolov8n.pt if not found

model = YOLO('yolov8n.pt')

  

# Train the model

model.train(data="/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/data.yaml", epochs=50, imgsz=640)

  

# Validation performance

metrics = model.val()

  

# Run inference

results = model.predict(source="/content/drive/My Drive/mosquito_hostspot_detection/dataset/images/val", save=True)
